1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with channel pairing and power allocation in a multichannel multihop relay network to enhance the end-to-end data rate. Information theory is concerned with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information, which is the main focus of this paper. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a multichannel multihop relay network, which is a networking problem. The paper proposes a solution to enhance the end-to-end data rate, which is a key performance metric in networking. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the joint optimization of channel pairing and power allocation, which is a control problem. The paper proposes a solution to optimize the performance of the system, which is a key objective of control systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with enhancing the end-to-end data rate, which is a key performance metric in multimedia applications. The paper proposes a solution to optimize the performance of a multichannel multihop relay network, which is a common infrastructure for multimedia applications.
